{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Enable and fund pay for special constables doing police duties during pandemic",
        "additional_details": "This would secure increased policing and provide work to special constables who maybe out of work due to the pandemic.\r\n \r\nThere is likely to be increased absence in the police through sickness and self isolating, support by special constables can ensure the public are kept safe and policing levels remain high.\r\n \r\nCurrently specials receive allowances of\r\n- Over 4 hours but not exceeding 8 hours: up to \u00a37.23\r\n- Over 8 hours but not exceeding 12 hours: up to \u00a314.66\r\n- Over 12 hours: up to \u00a324.15\r\n \r\nThe public need the support of their police, this also provides work for specials who maybe be absent due to closed businesses.",
        "background": "The Government should enable and fund pay for special constables at the same salary or an agreed daily wage to carry out policing duties during the current covid-19 pandemic.",
